verbose_text: As shown in XREF_FIG, high concentration insulin significantly upregulated the expression of p-ERK1/2, p-JNK, p-p38 MAPK and nuclear NF-kappaB / p65 in VSMCs compared with in the N + C-siRNA group (P < 0.05), whereas lenti-KDM3A-siRNA transduction into VSMCs markedly reduced the expression levels of p-ERK1/2, p-JNK, p-p38 MAPK and NF-kappaB / p65 by 26.01, 26.08, 33.56 and 24.00% compared with in the HI + C-siRNA group, respectively (P < 0.05).
evidence: expression of p-ERK1/2, p-JNK, p-p38 MAPK and nuclear NF-kappaB/p65
